uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.jdbc.filter

Interface FilterVisitor<X,T>

  • Type Parameters:
    X - return type of visitor
    T - type of filter.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseCombineFilter.AddFilterVisitor, CheckEmptyVisitor, ConvertPureAcceptFilterVisitor, DataObjectFactory.MakeRemoteFilterVisitor, FilterConverter, GetListFilterVisitor, MakeSelectVisitor, NegatingFilterVisitor, OptionalFilterConverter, TupleFactory.TupleAndFilter.AddMemberVisitor

    public interface FilterVisitor<X,T>
    A visitor for BaseFilter. We use the visitor pattern as this makes the dependencies between the type hierarchy and the code that uses them explicit. If a new sub-type of BaseFilter is introduced it has to either extend an existing sub-type and function only as that sub-type and/or have a new method added to the {link FilterVisitor} interface. This in turn ensures that all visitor logic needs to be updated to take account of the new type.

    Combinations of multiple sub-types should have an explicit interface and visit method because the visitor has to specify how to combine the different behaviours.
